  <static seed="160" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring640.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{0.25r-r^{3}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>r\mathopen{}\left(0.5+r\right)\mathopen{}\left(0.5-r\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Note that <m>r</m> is common to both terms- once we factor this term
out of the polynomial, the resulting expression is the <em>difference of squares</em></p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {0.25r-r^{3}} \amp  = r(0.5^2-{r}^2)\\
                            \amp  = {r\mathopen{}\left(0.5+r\right)\mathopen{}\left(0.5-r\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
